  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Finance Manager",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for an experienced <strong>Assistant Finance Manager</strong> to support financial operations, lead the accounts team, and ensure accurate reporting and compliance. The role works closely with management on budgeting, forecasting, and operational finance.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Manage monthly/annual financial reporting and analysis.</li><li>Support budgeting, forecasting, and cashflow planning.</li><li>Supervise the finance team and improve processes and controls.</li><li>Handle audit and tax matters with auditors and tax agents.</li><li>Review project financials, contract terms, and tender requirements.</li><li>Consolidate financial data for management reporting.</li><li>Liaise with internal teams and external stakeholders (banks, auditors, agencies).</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Degree in Accounting/Finance; professional certification preferred.</li><li>5+ years of relevant experience with team supervision.</li><li>Strong knowledge of reporting, budgeting, and compliance.</li><li>Good communication, analytical, and problem‑solving skills.</li><li>Able to work in a dynamic environment and manage expectations and tight deadlines.</li><li>Meticulous with an ‘eye’ for details and able to work independently.</li><li>Willing to hands on and able to work with all levels.</li><li>Preferable experience in import / export trading, manufacturing industry though criteria is not a must.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
